Strategy_resp: I imagined restaurants I've been to, and imagined how the process was when I was there. From entering the establishment, getting to my seats, ordering food, and eating it.
At first, I just wrote in the first things that came to mind, but then afterwards I tried going by categories such as animals.
I imagined objects in my own garage, and then that helped me think of associated objects. So if I thought of hammer, then of course I think of nails as well.

I imagined occupations that my family and I had in my life, and then thought about occupation of neighbors and in my daily life. I then tried to use associations with the occupations, such as security guard to bouncer to bartender.
I tried thinking of simple three letter words by thinking of each letter after A. Sometimes longer words would pop up as I do this.
I tried to imagine all the times I've gone to a hotel lobby, and what it looked like.
I tried thinking of common animals I see everyday, and then I started thinking of pets. I started think of zoo animals and then typical safari type animals.
I thought of sports that I see on TV and that I used to play myself.
After the first word, I thought of words that were either synonyms, antonyms, or rhymed with a previous word.
